	(50,3,'2013-08-01 20:36:52','2013-08-01 20:36:52','<em>Approximately 98% of all financial contribution goes toward preparing our students for a career in the maritime industry.</em>\n\nJoin The Anchor Program family and become a TAP Affiliate:\n\nIndividual donations are the way we are able to keep this program going, keep it successful, and changing lives each day through training and preparing our graduates for substantial careers; instilling hope, pride and a strong desire to achieve even more.\n\nIf your company has a matching gift program, suggest The Anchor Program for inclusion.\n\nAsk your employer to make a yearly financial commitment to TAP.\n\n\"Be the Anchor\" - Our scholarship program\nBe a sponsor for one of our students and enable them to succeed for a lifetime! You can also talk with your company about making an annual gift to \"Be the Anchor.\" Each dollar collected will assist students who are having difficulty paying the enrollment fees.\n\nOpportunity for Growth\n\nHelp us do even more! We are constantly receiving inquiries about the capability of bringing our programs into other areas. Right now, we offer the Basic Program in Oakland, CA and QMED in Seattle, WA, but we\'d love to offer both in both places! With financial contributotions from our TAP Affiliates, we will able to expand our service locations while beefing up the programs that are already in existence. Our goal is always to serve as many people as we can.','Donations','','publish','open','open','','donations','','','2013-08-01 20:36:52','2013-08-01 20:36:52','',0,'http://www.theanchorprogram.com/?page_id=50',0,'page','',0),
	(53,3,'2013-08-01 20:37:55','2013-08-01 20:37:55','<h3>Basic Maritime Program\nSF Bay Area, CA</h3>\nFor information related to\nthis program, contact:\nJohn Hastings\n510-992-3534\nMon-Fri\n12:00p-4:00p\n<h3><strong>QMED\nSeattle, WA</strong></h3>\nFor information related to\nthis course, contact the\ninstructor:\n\nJohn Hastings\n510-992-3545\nMon-Fri\n12:00p-5:00p\n\nMailing Address:\n\n1916 Pike Pl Suite 12\nSeattle, WA 98101','Contact and Locations','','publish','open','open','','locations-and-contact','','','2013-08-01 20:37:55','2013-08-01 20:37:55','',0,'http://www.theanchorprogram.com/?page_id=53',0,'page','',0),
	(58,3,'2013-08-01 20:41:28','2013-08-01 20:41:28','The age old idea about good works is that it is often spread through word of mouth, and that is how things grow, inspire and effect more and more people.\n\nThe Anchor Program strongly believes in this method of community collaboration for growth and achieving success. We have seen many people involved with this program travel through different streams and help in different ways. Some may make and individual contribution, and then decide they\'d like to get their hands dirty and volunteer. We\'ve had volunteers that have seen the positive influence of TAP, thus they began urging people learn about it and start the program.\n\n<strong>Join our movement by becoming a TAP Affiliate!</strong>\n\nThe Anchor Program is eager to develop relationships with community organizations, educational officials, church groups, and government agencies in order to support our movement, raise awareness, and provide new outlets for our youth. If you represent an organization, or simply would like to offer your assistance to our program, please contact one of our representatives today.','Become a TAP Affiliate','','publish','open','open','','become-a-tap-affiliate','','','2013-08-01 20:41:28','2013-08-01 20:41:28','',0,'http://www.theanchorprogram.com/?page_id=58',0,'page','',0),
	(60,3,'2013-08-01 20:42:32','2013-08-01 20:42:32','<h2>Our Mission</h2>\r\n<em><strong>The Anchor Program serves local communities by offering exposure to viable career choices for young adults, and others, whose options may be limited. </strong><strong>We provide a lifestyle alternative through training, certification, and preparation for a career in the growing maritime industry where graduates have the potential to earn a substantial salary, travel the world, and create a new career path.</strong></em>\r\n\r\nThe Anchor Program (TAP) is a 501(c)(3) non-profit service organization that prides itself on “training the mariners of tomorrow.” TAP provides vocational and life skills training to youth (aged 16+) and others interested in pursuing careers in the maritime industry; more specifically, the United States Merchant Marine.  Additional maritime training opportunities are also available.\r\n\r\nThe Maritime industry offers vast career opportunities worldwide each year. As of September 2010, the national unemployment rate was reported to be just a hair under 10% — a number that quickly doubles in inner cities and some of the harder hit areas of the country. With such an abysmal job market, it’s no wonder many disadvantaged youth turn to crime or other unsavory professions to pay the bills.\r\n\r\nThe goal of The Anchor Program is to reach out to those in need of a helping hand to help bridge the gap between the Maritime Industry and the unemployed members of our community. Our 60-day certificate program gives students both the classroom and on-deck training necessary to prepare anyone for entry-level positions in the maritime industry, as well as the option to enroll in post-secondary maritime training.\r\n<h2>Founder and CEO, John Hastings</h2>\r\nHailing from Richmond, CA,  John L. Hastings is the founder and executive director of The Anchor Program.  Mr. Hastings is a fourth generation merchant seaman whose great-grandfather, grandfather <em>and</em> father were all merchant marines. Their positive influence and support inspired John to follow in their footsteps, and at 16, he had already completed all of his entry-level training to head off to sea. John’s illustrious career in the maritime industry took him to hundreds of ports scatted around the world, and provided him with the hands-on experience that helped him to quickly advance to the role of engineer. After working for major shipping companies for most of his years, Mr. Hastings finally retired after 36-years from the U.S Department of Defense.\r\n\r\nLooking back, John remembers when his future didn’t look so bright. “When I was diagnosed with ADHD” he recalls, “it was the Maritime Industry that gave me the first opportunity to really make something out of myself.” Because of how much the maritime industry helped him become the man he is today, Mr. Hastings feels a personal obligation towards helping other young men and women who also feel like their future job outlook is bleak. Over a three-year period, The Anchor Program has successfully trained and placed hundreds of students in the merchant marine. More than 80% of the graduates have secured employment; the average starting salary being $45,000/year or more. Needless to say, Mr. Hastings is extremely proud of the the accomplishments of The Anchor Program.','Mission and Background','','publish','open','open','','mission','','','2015-02-13 22:59:40','2015-02-13 22:59:40','',0,'http://www.theanchorprogram.com/?page_id=60',0,'page','',0),
	(62,3,'2013-08-01 20:43:47','2013-08-01 20:43:47','','News and Updates','','publish','open','open','','news-and-updates','','','2013-08-01 20:43:47','2013-08-01 20:43:47','',0,'http://www.theanchorprogram.com/?page_id=62',0,'page','',0),
	(64,3,'2013-08-01 22:18:50','2013-08-01 22:18:50','<h3>Apply for the Basic Maritime program</h3>\n<h4>or <a class=\"read-more\" style=\"float: none; background-position: 97% 50%; background-size: 20px auto;\" href=\"http://dev.tap.local/wp/../wp-content/uploads/tap/2013/08/TAPBasicApp2013.pdf\">Download the application instead</a></h4>\n<div><!--cforms name=\"Application\"--></div>','Apply','','publish','open','open','','apply','','','2013-08-01 22:18:50','2013-08-01 22:18:50','',0,'http://www.theanchorprogram.com/?page_id=64',0,'page','',0),
	(97,3,'2013-08-02 00:23:05','2013-08-02 00:23:05','<h3><strong>Board Members</strong></h3>\n<strong>John Hastings</strong>\nFounder and CEO\n\n<strong>Tiffany Francies\n</strong>Student Development Director<strong>\n</strong>Tiffany obtained her Bachelor\'s degree in Social Work and is currently working on her Master\'s degree in Human Resources Management. Over the past couple of years she has dedicated a lot of her time to her church youth group at Delta Bay Church of Christ in the Pittsburg/Antioch area, providing life skills to prepare them for school, work, and the real world.  Tiffany looks forward to using her social work skills, youth group experience, and growing knowledge in Human Resource to help TAP students reach their goals and develop a career.\n\n<strong>Damon J. Hastings</strong>\nCreative Director\nAn Economics degree doesn’t exactly point to a career in design, but if you ask Damon, it makes perfect sense. The entire world is in some way built on the principles of economics. Understanding this, Damon designs processes that will allow companies to be more successful, artists to gain more exposure, and underprivileged individuals to gain access to new opportunities. With TAP, Damon strives to use his knowledge of both design and economics to help to bring more jobs to those who need them.\n\n<strong>Terence Hastings</strong>\nSocial Media Strategist\nTerence is a current business student and Veteran of the United States Navy. He is a Boiler House and Industrial Water Treatment Operator in the petroleum refining industry.\n\n<strong>Cochise Potts</strong>\nAdvisor to the Board, Treasury\n\n<strong>Shavon Tate</strong>\nWith a longstanding commitment to the success of The Anchor Program, over the years, Shavon has been involved on many levels. In 2007, she joined TAP as a volunteer, which led to a position as Executive Assistant. She held the position until 2010, and has since been an active board member and volunteer. She is currently a student working towards an AAS in medical office administration.\n\n<strong>Arielle Vaughan</strong>\nGrowth and Operations Director\nSince receiving her BA in Communications/PR, Arielle has experienced a variety of work, leading to a realization that her passion involves work that can make a beneficial impact on other people. In addition to TAP, Arielle is focused on providing for her family, taking courses in child development, and preparing a program to help young children realize their passion and utilize their talents in order to build a fulfilling life with happiness as the core.\n<h3><strong>Our Training Ships</strong></h3>\nBasic Program Training - Oakland/Richmond, CA\n\n<a href=\"http://www.uslhs.org/about_lightship.php\">Lightship LV 605, Relief</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.theanchorprogram.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/TempLightshipRelief.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-126\" alt=\"Lightship WAL-605, Relief, Embarcadero, Oakland, CA\" src=\"http://www.theanchorprogram.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/TempLightshipRelief-300x225.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"225\" /></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://www.ssredoakvictory.com/index.htm\">SS Red Oak Victory</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://dev.tap.local/wp/../wp-content/uploads/tap/2013/08/Red-Oak.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-124\" alt=\"Red Oak\" src=\"http://dev.tap.local/wp/../wp-content/uploads/tap/2013/08/Red-Oak-300x200.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"200\" /></a>\n\nQMED Program Training - Seattle/Edmonds, WA\n\n<a href=\"http://www.virginiav.org/history\">Virginia V</a>\n\n<a href=\"http://dev.tap.local/wp/../wp-content/uploads/tap/2013/08/Virginia-V.jpg\"><img class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-125\" alt=\"Virginia V\" src=\"http://dev.tap.local/wp/../wp-content/uploads/tap/2013/08/Virginia-V-300x201.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"201\" /></a>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','Meet Our Team','','publish','open','open','','meet-our-team','','','2013-08-02 00:23:05','2013-08-02 00:23:05','',0,'http://www.theanchorprogram.com/?page_id=97',0,'page','',0),
