	(135,3,'2013-08-07 17:26:32','2013-08-07 17:26:32','On October 12, 2012, The Anchor Program was proud and very excited to acquire The Relief, a Lightship which served as a floating lighthouse for the U.S. Coast Guard for 25 years. The Relief will soon host classes and provide an excellent training ground for our students - future mariners!. Please visit The United States Lighthouse Society\'s website<a href=\"http://www.uslhs.org/about_lightship.php\"> here </a>to learn more about our new ship.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;','Our New Ship','','publish','open','open','','aquisition-of-the-lightship-relief','','','2013-08-07 17:26:32','2013-08-07 17:26:32','',0,'http://www.theanchorprogram.com/?p=135',0,'post','',0),
	(143,3,'2013-08-07 22:39:52','2013-08-07 22:39:52','One success story comes from Mr. Mickle Elliott. “When I moved to California from Louisiana to make a fresh start it was hard. No one wanted to hire a 61-year-old man!” It was The Anchor Program that gave Mr. Elliott the big break he needed. After completing TAP’s 90-day program, Mr. Elliot quickly landed his first with a ship repair company that sent him to repair U.S. Coast Guard vessels in Hawaii.','Testimonies','','publish','open','open','','testimonies','','','2013-08-07 22:39:52','2013-08-07 22:39:52','',0,'http://www.theanchorprogram.com/?page_id=143',0,'page','',0),
